content:
I just uploaded an extension (made with Forge) to Simplifier, and I am totally stumped by the validation error "Incomplete : Resolution of profile at 'http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/StructureDefinition' failed: Type checking the data: Encountered unknown element 'valueSetReference' at location 'StructureDefinition.snapshot[0].element[4].binding[0].valueSetReference[0]' while parsing"

the extension is here: https://simplifier.net/UFP/Planet/~xml
Your project seems to be an R4 project, but there is still a dependency on the STU3 Core packages. Could you try upgrading these first and check if the error can be reproduced?
Jupp. I just noticed the dependencies! They're changed now and the error is gone. Thanks!
Although. Apparently I can delete dependencies from my project, but I can't add them. Weird...
Ah. now it works... must have hit "cancel" by accident. It's just too hot over here...
